In a call between President Obama and Prime Minister Cameron of the United Kingdom, they discussed various global matters. They expressed concern about the Syrian government's violence against civilians and agreed on the need to stop the bloodshed. They also discussed recent developments in the global financial system, Libya, and Afghanistan. Prime Minister Cameron expressed condolences for the loss of life in the U.S. helicopter incident in Afghanistan, and they both welcomed the return of public order in British cities after days of looting and violence.